==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''Greek numeral''' (''plural'' '''Greek numerals''')

# A system of [[numeral]]s represented using letters of the [[Greek alphabet]]. These are used for special purposes, where in English [[Roman numerals]] are used, these include:
#: ο Γεώργιος Ε' = George V,  ο Μιχαήλ Η' = Michael VIII
#: Τόμος Β' = Volume 2
#: στον ΙΖ' αιώνα = the 17th century.